<P>The Real-Time Systems research group is headed by <A HREF="mok.html">Prof.
Aloysius Mok</A>. In the past few years, we have worked towards laying
the groundwork for establishing a firm theoretical foundation for real-time
systems and also to build design tools based on this foundation. Our work
can be categorized into three areas as follows: </P>

<UL>
<LI>Specification and Modeling: precise formulation of real-time properties
of systems. </LI>

<LI>Analysis and Verification: reasoning about real-time properties. </LI>

<LI>Synthesis: enforcing stringent timing constraints and other real-time
properties. </LI>
</UL>

